Chocolate Souffle with Orange Sauce

Souffle:
1/2 tbsp unsalted butter, softened
1/4 c sugar, divided
4 oz bittersweet chocolate cut into 1/2" pieces
3/4 c heavy cream
4 egg whites
confectioners' sugar for garnish

Preheat oven to 400F. Grease 4 6oz ramekins with the butter and coat with 2 tbsp of the sugar, rotating to coat the entire ramekin. In a double boiler, add the chocolate and crea,, and heat until completely melted, stirring until smooth. In a stand mixer fitted with a whisk attachment, add the egg whites and beat until soft peaks have formed. Add the remaining 2 tbsp of sugar and whisk until stiff peaks have formed. Working in 3 batches, carefully fold the chocolate mixture into the egg whites using a rubber spatula. Divide the batter among the prepared ramekins. Place the souffles on a baking sheet and bake until set in the center, 13-15 min. 

Sauce:
1/2 c sour cream
1/4 c oj
1 tbsp sugar
1 tsp orange zest
1 tsp confectioners' sugar

Whisk all the ingredients in a small bowl until smooth.


Remove the souffles from the oven. Dust with confectioners sugar and spoon over the orange sauce. Serve warm.
